Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.12,0:23:38.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们将你放上雪橇 把你弹入太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They put you on a sled and slingshot you into space...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.54,0:23:41.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以这样的方式 小行星微弱的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in such a way that the weak gravity of the asteroid...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.79,0:23:45.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会把你拉入轨道 然而却不会将你再送回来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will hold you in orbit, but won't pull you back down again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.96,0:23:47.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那将是个了不起的搭乘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt would be a great ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.63,0:23:52.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,火星距离的三倍远的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Three times farther away than Mars...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.38,0:23:55.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星的轨道上 是其拥挤的卫星系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the orbit of Jupiter, with its crowded moon system...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.60,0:23:58.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,呈现出数十种不同的景观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}offers dozens of diverse visions.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.89,0:24:01.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它有可能为未来的游客带来诱惑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt may prove tempting forfuture travelers...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.64,0:24:04.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 一个往返可能就需要5年的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but a round trip could take five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.48,0:24:09.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,土星几乎是木星的两倍远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn is nearly twice as far as Jupiter...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.53,0:24:13.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,10年旅游的念头可能太过分了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the thought of decade-long trips might be too much to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.91,0:24:17.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而科技能够分割时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there are technologies...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.78,0:24:22.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,使得参观火星就几天工夫\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can slice the time it takes to visit Mars tojust a few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.17,0:24:30.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对于人类冒险闯入宇宙深处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For mankind ever to venture into the depths of the cosmos...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.09,0:24:34.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尝试沐浴在异域恒星的星光中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}endeavor to bathe in the light of an exotic star...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.34,0:24:38.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,乃至就在我们太阳系的郊区巡游\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or evenjust to voyage to the suburbs of our own solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.85,0:24:42.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们需要找到一种非常非常快捷的出游方式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we'll need to find a way to travel much, much faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.35,0:24:46.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,出游最快的方式是什么呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's the fastest we could travel?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.19,0:24:49.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学已经断言没有什么能够跑的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nothing yet observed by science moves faster...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.61,0:24:54.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,快过光速 每秒18.6英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than the speed of light, 186,000 miles per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.11,0:24:59.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,光速是宇宙间的终极速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The speed of light is the ultimate velocity in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.58,0:25:01.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是爱因斯坦定下的规矩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's Einstein's cop on the block.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.37,0:25:08.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,光速使你绕地球跑七圈只需一秒钟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The speed of light is so fast that you could go around the Earth...seven times in just one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.59,0:25:11.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你以光速跳上月球的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For you to jump to the Moon, at the speed of light...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.38,0:25:13.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,抵达月球就一秒钟的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you could reach the Moon in about one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.38,0:25:19.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,与之相比 以目前的科技则需要三天才能到达那里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Compare that to the three days it takes...to get there with current technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.39,0:25:24.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,问题是我们无法以光速出行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The problem is that we can't travel at the speed of light...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.85,0:25:27.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,甚至还没有什么能接近它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or really anything even approaching it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.90,0:25:31.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,拿我们曾经发送过的最快的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Take the fastest thing we have ever sent anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.36,0:25:37.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来问一下 去最近的恒星需要多长的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and ask how long will that take to reach the nearest stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.24,0:25:38.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那需要5万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That would take 50,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.91,0:25:44.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是利用现有化学推进技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that is using current chemical propulsion...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.58,0:25:48.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其最高纪录是时速4万英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which maxes out at about 40,000 miles per hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.58,0:25:53.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们用来让火箭离开地球的能量是一样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the same power source we use...to lift our rockets off of the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.51,0:25:59.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而要让我们前往火星快上几个月\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But getting us to Mars faster than a few months' time...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.14,0:26:01.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就需要别的推进方式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would require a different kind of propulsion.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.81,0:26:05.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有了一些想法 如何让我们的推进\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are a few ideas for how to propel us...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.14,0:26:08.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,速度更接近光速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to velocities closer to the speed of light...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.31,0:26:09.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,能够快到足以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which would be fast enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.60,0:26:13.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,把我们在一天内送达太阳系的任何一个地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to get us anywhere in the solar system in under a day...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.23,0:26:16.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以致在10年内抵达最近的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or even to the nearest stars in less than a decade.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.28,0:26:19.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,回想一个理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One such theory echoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.78,0:26:22.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,俗世古老的推进装置:\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an ancient earthly propulsion device:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.70,0:26:24.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,风帆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wind pushing a sail.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.70,0:26:27.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是伟大的天文学家开普勒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt was Kepler, that great astronomer...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.66,0:26:29.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,首先在他的笔记中提到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who first wrote down in his notes...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.50,0:26:33.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有可能利用风帆扬帆在外太空中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the possibility of using sails to sail in outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.63,0:26:37.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来自太阳的光流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Light streaming from the Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.38,0:26:39.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,酷似外太空中的阵阵凉风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}mimics gusts of wind in outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.39,0:26:46.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种太阳风就是彗星接近太阳时创造其尾巴的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This solarwind is what creates a comet's tail as it nears the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.89,0:26:51.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可是 阳光是四面八方散开的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, sunlight scatters in all directions...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.27,0:26:53.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,与太阳的距离增加一倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and as the distance from the Sun doubles...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.94,0:26:56.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其能量则会减少四倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its power reduces by a factor of four.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.99,0:26:59.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,凭借月球的少许帮助\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With a little help from the Moon...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.78,0:27:03.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就会有一种情况 光可以集中在一个方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there is a manner in which light could be focused in one direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.41,0:27:08.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果我们在月球上有一组激光炮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf we have a battery of laser cannons on the Moon...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.75,0:27:13.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对准太阳帆同步开炮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}firing in synchronization at a solar sail...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.50,0:27:15.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们就有可能推进它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we may be able to propel it...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.17,0:27:18.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许可以达到光速的一半\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to about perhaps half the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.21,0:27:21.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现在 激光会在太空中弥散开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, lasers do diffuse with space.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.34,0:27:23.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比如 我在地球上有一个激光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For example, if l have a laser on the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.80,0:27:25.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,射向月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and l shine it to the Moon...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.14,0:27:27.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它不会在月球上产生一个光斑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it does not create a spot on the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.56,0:27:30.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个光斑在月球上会有5英里宽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The spot is about five miles across on the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.65,0:27:33.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些风帆无论如何将会很巨大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These sails, however, would be huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.52,0:27:36.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现在我们谈到了宇航员\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now we're talking about astronauts...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.44,0:27:39.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许要在外太空度过数月\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}perhaps spending months in outer space...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.11,0:27:43.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,布置一个数百英里 甚至数千英里宽的风帆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}designing a sail hundreds..maybe even thousands of miles across...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.87,0:27:50.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,轻巧耐用 目的是为了采集月球上的激光炮发出的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sufficiently light and durable in order to capture light...from a battery of laser beams on the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.17,0:27:55.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不过太阳风帆把太空旅行的目的地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But solar sailing limits space vessels...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.34,0:27:58.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,局限在了太阳系里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to destinations within our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.21,0:28:00.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,回避这个问题 有一个替代方案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One alternative gets around this problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.38,0:28:04.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是利用氢 宇宙中最丰富的元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by tapping into hydrogen...the most abundant element in the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.84,0:28:06.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来作为推进能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as a propulsion source.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.31,0:28:10.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我最中意的送我们去恒星的方案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}My favorite design to take us to the stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.23,0:28:12.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是核聚变喷气发动机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the ramjet fusion engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.36,0:28:19.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种喷气发动机在其正前方有一个巨大的戽斗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ramjet engine has a gigantic scoop...in the forward direction...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.73,0:28:23.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在其在深太空行进时吞下氢气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that gobbles up hydrogen gas as it moves in deep space.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.07,0:28:25.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它收集氢气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt collects the hydrogen gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.37,0:28:27.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后像太阳那样将它聚合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then fuses it just like the Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.99,0:28:31.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在其另一端射出巨大的离子流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and shoots out a huge stream of ions out the other end.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.91,0:28:33.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,理论上看来很棒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And on paper, it looks fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.92,0:28:37.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,理论上看来好像核聚变喷气发动机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On paper it looks as if a ramjet fusion engine...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.09,0:28:40.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可以永久运行 只是在消耗氢气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could go on forever, simply using up the hydrogen...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.96,0:28:43.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,外太空里比比皆是的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that is found naturally in outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.34,0:28:48.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,很遗憾 科学家在实验中尚未达到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unfortunately, scientists have not yet been able to achieve...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.81,0:28:52.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对氢核聚变反应的可控能力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a hydrogen fusion reaction capable of propulsion in tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.94,0:28:56.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而另一个潜在的能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But another potential fuel source...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.86,0:28:59.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,好像是科幻小说中出现的那种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one that seems to come right out of science fiction...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.73,0:29:02.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,已经在实验室里创造出来了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has already been created in laboratories.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.24,0:29:05.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它叫做反物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's called anti-matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.24,0:29:08.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它与我们所知的一切刚好相反\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's the opposite of all that we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.66,0:29:13.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比如 思考一下镜像里的世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For example, think of the world...on the other side of the looking glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.46,0:29:16.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像是刘易斯·卡罗尔的《爱丽斯漫游仙境》\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just like in Lewis Carroll's "Alice in Wonderland"...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.17,0:29:19.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的物理学家一直在想\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we physicists have wondered, is there another universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.25,0:29:21.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,镜子里另一头的宇宙是否是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the other end of the looking glass...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.25,0:29:22.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个完全倒过来的宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a parity-reversed universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.84,0:29:25.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在那里左变成了右 而右变成了左了呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where left becomes right, right becomes left?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.68,0:29:29.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在反宇宙中电荷是反过来的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln an anti-universe, charges are reversed...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.05,0:29:31.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以正电荷变成了负电荷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so positive charges become negative...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.56,0:29:33.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,负电荷变成了正电荷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}negative charges become positive...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.18,0:29:37.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦它们相遇就会产生能量爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and when they meet, they create a burst of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.48,0:29:41.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 如果镜子里的另一头是宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if this universe on the other side of the looking glass...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.40,0:29:42.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是反物质构成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were made out of anti-matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.86,0:29:46.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我一旦接触到这个宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and l were to touch this other universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.86,0:29:49.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我就会在能量大爆发中摧毁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l would destroy...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.20,0:29:53.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,纽约的大部分城区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}most of the NewYork City metropolitan area...in a burst of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.29,0:30:00.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此 反物质和物质转换成能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the conversion of anti-matter and matter to energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.34,0:30:02.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是百分之百的高效\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is one hundred percent efficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.17,0:30:10.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是终极发动机 但还存在一个隐情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt is the ultimate engine, but there is a catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.14,0:30:11.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,总是隐情不断\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's always a catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.85,0:30:14.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,即使我们能够在实验室里创造出反物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even though we can create anti-atoms in the laboratory...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.81,0:30:17.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其成本是相当惊人的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the cost is stupendous.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.39,0:30:20.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能让美国破产\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt would bankrupt the United States of America...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.27,0:30:23.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,才能创造出一茶匙反物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to create a teaspoon of anti-matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.78,0:30:26.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不管怎样只需要几克反物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, it would only take a few grams of anti-matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.74,0:30:28.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就能将我们送往火星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to take us to Mars...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.20,0:30:30.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许几茶匙反物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and perhaps several teaspoons of anti-matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.66,0:30:32.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就能将我们送往附近的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to take us to the nearby stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.50,0:30:39.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而我们只要是去访问遥远的恒星或另一个星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But for us to evervisit...a distant star or another galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.87,0:30:41.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们所需要的东西就甚至要比爱丽丝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we need something stranger...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.54,0:30:45.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,凝视她的镜子所渴求的更为陌生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than even Alice could ever dream of...peering through her looking glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.05,0:30:54.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家孜孜以求推进的方法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists continue the quest for a propulsion method...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.68,0:30:57.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,把我们不断送入更深的太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to carry us ever deeper into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.39,0:31:03.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是即使达到了光速 也不会让我们走得更远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But even achieving light-speed won't allow us to get very far.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.94,0:31:10.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,光很快 然而宇宙太大了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Light's fast, but the universe is huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.32,0:31:16.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 即使我们能够搭乘上光束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, even If we could ride on a beam of light...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.24,0:31:18.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果我们想要穿越星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we wanted to cross the galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.08,0:31:20.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们所做的一切都已经在科幻小说中安排了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the way they do in all the science fiction programs...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.58,0:31:22.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将需要10万年的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would take 100,000 years to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.13,0:31:28.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,即使以光速前往最近的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And even at light-speed, traveling to the nearest galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.26,0:31:30.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也需要几百万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would take several million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.43,0:31:35.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果光速是宇宙的速度的极限\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if light-speed is the ultimate speed limit of the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.05,0:31:37.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看来我们命中注定限制在了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it seems we are doomed to confinement...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.56,0:31:39.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的银河系周围了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in our galactic neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.89,0:31:41.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们迫切需要的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What we're desperate for...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.35,0:31:44.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是对时空结构的一些新的认识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is some new understanding of the fabric of space-time...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.44,0:31:47.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,能让我们设法弯曲它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that will allow us to somehow warp it...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.28,0:31:49.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,扭曲它 以便我们能够走捷径\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}distort it so that you can take shortcuts...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.57,0:31:51.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当然 那是他们在《星际迷航》中的情景\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, of course, that's what they do in "Star Trek"...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.95,0:31:54.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那时他们打开了他们的翘曲飞行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when they turn on theirwarp drives.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.37,0:31:57.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们想从星系的一面到另外一面去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They want to get from one side of the galaxy to the other...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.79,0:31:59.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们所做的一切就是调用翘曲飞行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all they do is invoke the warp drive...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.37,0:32:01.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来弯曲太空组织\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that warps the fabric of space...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.79,0:32:03.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后他们就在那里找到了一点捷径\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then they take a little shortcut right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.54,0:32:04.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们实际上是在耍手腕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They cheat, basically.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.67,0:32:08.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大家都知道爱因斯坦的名言:\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Everybody knows Einstein's famous dictum...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.17,0:32:10.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你无法超过光速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"You cannot go faster than the speed of light".
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.80,0:32:13.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可是它有一个脚注\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, there's a footnote to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.18,0:32:16.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你看 爱因斯坦还是留有余地的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You see, Einstein left open the possibility that you can...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.43,0:32:19.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你可以撕裂折叠时空本身的结构\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rip, fold the fabric of space and time itself...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.97,0:32:23.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这样你实际上获得了一条通行宇宙的捷径\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that you effectively take a shortcut through the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.02,0:32:26.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,想想地毯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Think of a carpet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.44,0:32:27.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你想穿过地毯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf you want to go across the carpet...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.02,0:32:29.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那可是老式的办法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's the old-fashioned way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.94,0:32:31.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你也可以用上一个套索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can also get a lasso...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.57,0:32:34.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,套住地毯另一头的桌子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and lasso a table on the other side of the carpet...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.07,0:32:36.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后将桌子拽向你\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then drag the table toward you...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.45,0:32:39.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那样你就将空间折叠在了你的面前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that you collapse the space in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.54,0:32:43.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,简而言之 爱因斯坦说 质量越大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln a nutshell, Einstein says the bigger the mass...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.58,0:32:45.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其对时空的弯曲也就越大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the bigger the bending of space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.75,0:32:50.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你将极大的能量浓缩到一点上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf you can concentrate...enormous amounts of energy at a single point...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.84,0:32:54.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,类似于黑洞或超大星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}comparable to that of a black hole...or a huge, gigantic star...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.68,0:32:58.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你实际上在弯曲时空的结构\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you are literallywarping the fabric of space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.93,0:33:01.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你只要跳到附近的恒星上去了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You simply hop across to the nearby stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.02,0:33:05.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以换句话说 你不用真的到那些恒星去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, in otherwords, you did not really go to the stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.85,0:33:07.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们会过来的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the stars came to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.94,0:33:11.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为你压缩了你前面的空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because you are compressing the space in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.65,0:33:17.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,需要大量的能量或质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The massive amount of energy or mass needed...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.37,0:33:19.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来创造这样一个弯曲的空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to create such a warped curvature of space...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.95,0:33:22.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,似乎令人费解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}seems beyond comprehension...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.20,0:33:25.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许超越了人类的能力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and perhaps beyond human capability.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.58,0:33:27.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也许有一种选择\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There may be an alternative.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.71,0:33:32.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,物理学家约翰.勃兰登堡在发展一个理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Physicist John Brandenburg is developing a theory...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.67,0:33:34.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其中未来的星际飞船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in which a starship of the future...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.67,0:33:37.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可以实现超光速飞行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could achieve faster-than-light travel...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.26,0:33:39.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,并非通过操控宇宙的大片区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not by manipulating a vast area of the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.89,0:33:44.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而是指操控飞船周围的空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but rather by manipulating only the area around the starship.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.60,0:33:49.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,诀窍在于将飞船模仿成一个奇怪的粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The trick is to have a starship imitate a curious particle...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.48,0:33:51.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当然 迄今为止 还只是理论上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that, so far, only exists in theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.40,0:33:54.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它叫做超子(超光速粒子)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's called a tachyon.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.03,0:33:57.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是能各种旋转的粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's a particle with a different twist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.57,0:34:01.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,光本身的速度是恒定的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Light itself always moves at the same speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.20,0:34:06.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,另一方面超子可以跑得无限快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tachyons, on the other hand, can go infinitely fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.46,0:34:09.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们就是无法慢于光速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They just can't go slower than the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.42,0:34:14.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们视光速为自己无法逾越的速度底线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They look at the speed of light...as a lower speed limit that they cannot violate.
